slots.description: The label displayed above the navigation element describing it's function.  Defaults to "Jump to section".
slots.name: heading

slots.description: The component creates a mirror shadowRoot based on the light DOM markup provided in the default slot.

members.name: events
members.description: List of all events in the component

members.name: breakpoint
members.description:
Breakpoint object mapping human-readable size names to viewport sizes
To overwrite this at the component-level, include `static get breakpoint` in your component's class definition

members.name: autobuild
members.description: Flips the switch on the component to create its own markup for the navigation. You can add `pfe-jump-links-panel__section` to each section that should show in the nav. If you want to use sub-sections add `has-sub-section` to the parent section that should always show and the `sub-section` class to the children of that section. If you use this attribute, keep in mind that non-JavaScript environments (some search engines, browsers with JS disabled) will not see the proper markup.

members.name: horizontal
members.description: Horizontal

members.name: stuck
members.description: Stickiness state

members.name: noHeader
members.description: Opt-out of the header region

members.name: srText
members.description: This attribute is read when the component upgrades to provide the innerText of the heading. If there is no `sr-text` attribute then the component defaults to "JUMP TO SECTION". This attribute is to enable translations and internationalization.

members.name: color
members.description: Color

members.name: offset
members.description: This attribute determines the distance from the top of the browser window to trigger a switch from one link being active to the next. For instance `offset="600"` would mean that threshold flips at 600px from the top. The default is set at 200, and if you desire 200px then you can leave this attribute off. The `offset` attribute should be placed on `pfe-jump-links-panel`. There is a css solution to control the offset, however the attribute value takes precedence over css. To read more about a css solution see below.
